18
00:02:04,623 --> 00:02:08,256
My lord! My lord, no! My lord!

19
00:02:09,049 --> 00:02:11,080
You're just the beginning, Fueang!

20
00:02:11,503 --> 00:02:15,103
Everything he holds dear,
I'll destroy it all.

21
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:16,560
You bastard!

22
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:20,843
No matter what,
Dech must come back to me

23
00:02:21,097 --> 00:02:23,097
and atone for what he did to me!

24
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:24,530
If you fail again,

25
00:02:25,243 --> 00:02:26,640
your son will die.

26
00:02:45,937 --> 00:02:46,937
Dech!

27
00:02:47,663 --> 00:02:49,000
You startled me.

28
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:50,710
You didn't make a sound.

29
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,950
You're too easily scared,
Ms. Malai.

30
00:02:54,677 --> 00:02:57,120
Who else would be here
but you and me?

31
00:03:00,357 --> 00:03:01,397
You're right.

32
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:03,970
What's going on?

33
00:03:04,737 --> 00:03:06,200
Why are you being so nice?

34
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,640
I found a way for us to start over.

35
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:11,970
How?

36
00:03:12,837 --> 00:03:14,970
I've noticed you're a good cook.

37
00:03:15,510 --> 00:03:17,843
So I figured we'd rent a row house
near the market

38
00:03:17,983 --> 00:03:19,280
and sell hot meals.

39
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,650
Is that a good idea?

40
00:03:20,997 --> 00:03:23,010
The market is full of people.

41
00:03:23,523 --> 00:03:25,290
What if someone recognizes me?

42
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,440
I checked it out.

43
00:03:28,203 --> 00:03:31,170
The morning customers
are either the locals

44
00:03:31,423 --> 00:03:33,483
or servants of powerful people.

45
00:03:34,343 --> 00:03:36,130
No one will recognize you.

46
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:38,920
It's not impossible.

47
00:03:39,537 --> 00:03:42,064
What if the viscount finds out?

48
00:03:42,176 --> 00:03:43,840
He'll never find out.

49
00:03:44,743 --> 00:03:49,080
Besides, I already spent
my life savings on the rent.

50
00:03:50,070 --> 00:03:51,070
Gee, Dech.

51
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:55,160
You're not mad I took
the liberty of doing that, right?

52
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,960
Not at all.

53
00:03:58,973 --> 00:04:01,760
On the contrary, it's good
you could manage all that.

54
00:04:02,230 --> 00:04:03,743
The idea never occurred to me.

55
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:09,240
So what food
do you think I should sell?

56
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:12,800
There are many dishes in my head.

57
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,320
Easy dishes like...

58
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:18,120
boiled eggs in sweet brown sauce,

59
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,480
spicy and sour soup.

60
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:22,320
or stir-fried minced pork
with salted fish.

61
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:27,097
These aren't
your favorite dishes, are they?

62
00:04:28,553 --> 00:04:30,040
Jeez, Ms. Malai.

63
00:04:30,713 --> 00:04:32,680
Even if they're not
my favorite dishes,

64
00:04:33,783 --> 00:04:36,480
everything you make is delicious.

65
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,800
Such a sweet talker.

66
00:04:42,377 --> 00:04:43,377
Ms. Malai.

67
00:04:49,590 --> 00:04:51,080
Thank you very much, Dech.

68
00:04:54,837 --> 00:04:57,280
Thank you for giving me a new life.

69
00:04:58,483 --> 00:04:59,723
Without you,

70
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,600
I don't know if, in this life,

71
00:05:03,663 --> 00:05:07,120
I would ever get to live
the way I wanted to.

72
00:05:15,243 --> 00:05:17,243
I should be thanking you

73
00:05:18,203 --> 00:05:20,703
for giving me courage
to break free from the viscount.

74
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:24,030
Otherwise, my life would have been dictated
by my debt for the rest of my life.

75
00:05:57,076 --> 00:05:59,960
Please make good on your promise
about letting Fueang and me leave.

76
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:02,733
Are you sure you're leaving
with just Fueang,

77
00:06:03,262 --> 00:06:04,952
and not my wife as well?

78
00:06:05,275 --> 00:06:07,852
If you mean
Ms. Malai who is my wife,

79
00:06:08,236 --> 00:06:09,526
you understand correctly.

80
00:06:10,035 --> 00:06:11,035
Dech!

81
00:06:50,537 --> 00:06:51,574
You must swear

82
00:06:52,323 --> 00:06:54,940
that you will only have
a physical relationship with Malai.

83
00:06:56,029 --> 00:06:58,960
But you must love only me.

84
00:07:01,177 --> 00:07:02,787
I swear that

85
00:07:03,076 --> 00:07:04,076
I will love

86
00:07:04,087 --> 00:07:05,843
and be faithful to His Lordship.

87
00:07:06,043 --> 00:07:07,937
If one day Dech breaks his promise,

88
00:07:08,212 --> 00:07:10,432
he will die with excruciating pain

89
00:07:11,061 --> 00:07:12,634
for hurting my feelings.

90
00:07:16,223 --> 00:07:17,423
No matter what,

91
00:07:18,117 --> 00:07:20,560
you will keep
your promise to me, Dech.

92
00:07:21,257 --> 00:07:23,320
I'll never let you
be happy with anyone

93
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:24,963
but me.

94
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,640
If our shop thrives,

95
00:07:52,197 --> 00:07:54,520
we'll need a couple more helpers.

96
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,120
You're hiring more people
before we open our shop?

97
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:02,040
I don't mean hired help.

98
00:08:03,307 --> 00:08:04,307
Dech!

99
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:06,383
You have a dirty mind.

100
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:08,320
I'm not being dirty.

101
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,557
Just imagine.

102
00:08:10,883 --> 00:08:13,600
If we have a couple of kids
running around,

103
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:15,320
it would be nice.

104
00:08:16,423 --> 00:08:17,823
One boy and one girl?

105
00:08:20,003 --> 00:08:23,376
Let's think about it
when our shop is actually thriving.

106
00:08:26,177 --> 00:08:28,280
But I want to think about it now.

107
00:08:28,903 --> 00:08:29,903
Dech.

108
00:08:32,557 --> 00:08:33,557
Picture it.

109
00:08:34,517 --> 00:08:37,350
If we have a girl,
she will look a lot like you.

110
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,520
She will be so adorable.

111
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:46,070
If we have a boy...

112
00:08:48,117 --> 00:08:49,600
he'll be reliable like you.

113
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,223
It'd be nice if he's the oldest.

114
00:08:53,710 --> 00:08:55,880
So he'd take care
of his little sister.

115
00:08:57,550 --> 00:08:59,710
I'd raise him to be
nothing like my brother.

116
00:09:02,207 --> 00:09:03,480
I'll help you.

117
00:09:03,863 --> 00:09:06,720
If he picks on his sister,
I'll punish him harshly.

118
00:09:09,077 --> 00:09:10,230
If he hates you

119
00:09:10,676 --> 00:09:12,690
but loves me
and comes to me for comfort,

120
00:09:12,917 --> 00:09:14,050
you'll be screwed.

121
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Great.

122
00:09:16,457 --> 00:09:18,837
I'll let you comfort me
about him hating me.

123
00:09:19,443 --> 00:09:20,443
Dech!

124
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:23,720
You always take advantage
for your own benefit.

125
00:09:34,037 --> 00:09:35,080
From now on,

126
00:09:35,883 --> 00:09:37,883
our lives will know only happiness.

127
00:09:40,383 --> 00:09:44,056
I'll do everything to make sure
that happens, Ms. Malai.

128
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:05,950
I'm sorry, Dech.

129
00:10:40,783 --> 00:10:42,080
What happened, Dech?

130
00:10:44,163 --> 00:10:46,360
I'm smelling smoke, Ms. Malai.

131
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:49,380
Fire!

132
00:10:50,693 --> 00:10:51,693
Fire!

133
00:10:54,599 --> 00:10:55,746
Move, I'm begging you.

134
00:10:55,947 --> 00:10:56,947
I'm not moving.

135
00:10:57,220 --> 00:11:00,193
If you're gonna shoot,
kill me along with Ms. Malai.

136
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:01,267
I can't!

137
00:11:01,447 --> 00:11:05,980
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

138
00:11:06,432 --> 00:11:10,979
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

139
00:11:12,406 --> 00:11:13,639
There's fire, Ms. Malai.

140
00:11:14,386 --> 00:11:16,720
How's that possible?
We're the only people here.

141
00:11:17,419 --> 00:11:19,320
Let's just leave first, Ms. Malai.

142
00:11:25,796 --> 00:11:26,960
Hurry, Ms. Malai.

143
00:11:38,043 --> 00:11:39,323
What's going on?

144
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:46,160
We were fooled.

145
00:11:47,130 --> 00:11:49,040
Who would fool us?

146
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,280
Ms. Malai, watch out!

147
00:12:16,283 --> 00:12:17,283
Move.

148
00:12:25,523 --> 00:12:27,183
Fueang's here, my lord.

149
00:12:30,357 --> 00:12:31,380
Thanks, Saeng.

150
00:12:31,617 --> 00:12:33,960
Leave us.
I'll call if I need something.

151
00:12:34,397 --> 00:12:35,397
Yes, sir.

152
00:12:45,497 --> 00:12:46,920
You had Saeng release me.

153
00:12:47,323 --> 00:12:48,880
You're probably thinking...

154
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:51,790
Kam killed Ms. Malai successfully.

155
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:56,560
You're really too smart
to be a servant.

156
00:13:00,509 --> 00:13:01,509
Let go!

157
00:13:02,077 --> 00:13:03,160
Come here. Don't move!

158
00:13:05,177 --> 00:13:06,720
Why are you fighting me?

159
00:13:08,006 --> 00:13:09,723
You responded to me too.

160
00:13:10,579 --> 00:13:11,579
Perv!

161
00:13:13,206 --> 00:13:14,760
Instead of calling me names,

162
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:17,503
you should be thanking me

163
00:13:18,237 --> 00:13:19,600
for reuniting you and Dech.

164
00:13:19,850 --> 00:13:22,360
Someone like you
will never be loved by anyone.

165
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:24,543
The more you behave this way,

166
00:13:24,577 --> 00:13:26,470
the more Dech will hate you.

167
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:27,830
Let him hate me.

168
00:13:28,417 --> 00:13:29,600
Because no matter what,

169
00:13:30,157 --> 00:13:32,397
I'm the one who owns his life.

170
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,200
He can't refuse me.

171
00:13:34,317 --> 00:13:36,210
There's nowhere for him to run.

172
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:43,520
Pathetic.

173
00:13:44,497 --> 00:13:47,600
You might appear to be
a man who has everything.

174
00:13:48,917 --> 00:13:51,400
But your heart is darker
than everything.

175
00:13:51,763 --> 00:13:54,516
How can anyone
love someone like that?

176
00:13:55,103 --> 00:13:56,103
Fueang!

177
00:13:57,517 --> 00:13:58,720
You crossed the line!

178
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:03,470
You can't handle me
telling the truth, my lord?

179
00:14:03,803 --> 00:14:05,636
You committed so many sins.

180
00:14:05,857 --> 00:14:09,470
You've done nothing but evil.
Karma will catch up with you!

181
00:14:09,777 --> 00:14:11,670
-Stop talking, Fueang!
-I won't!

182
00:14:13,417 --> 00:14:15,417
All you do is flex your power.

183
00:14:15,976 --> 00:14:17,123
No compassion.

184
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:20,080
One day you will die alone

185
00:14:20,597 --> 00:14:22,120
with none who loves you

186
00:14:22,190 --> 00:14:23,320
and all who hate you!

187
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:24,363
Fueang!

188
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:30,480
Mark my words, my lord.

189
00:14:31,247 --> 00:14:33,860
You will be alone as a homosexual.

190
00:14:34,447 --> 00:14:37,000
No one will truly love you.

191
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:40,280
No matter how much money you have,

192
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:42,760
you will die a pathetic death!

193
00:14:43,073 --> 00:14:44,073
Fueang!

194
00:14:45,153 --> 00:14:46,320
Stop talking!

195
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:58,720
Ms. Malai.

196
00:15:00,287 --> 00:15:01,287
Ms. Malai.

197
00:15:06,206 --> 00:15:07,206
Dech!

198
00:15:10,317 --> 00:15:11,317
Ms. Malai!

199
00:15:11,862 --> 00:15:13,183
Are you okay, Ms. Malai?

200
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,750
Don't move.

201
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,133
If you don't want to die.

202
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,760
If you're gonna kill Ms. Malai,

203
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,540
you have to kill me first.

204
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:26,540
Move!

205
00:15:26,693 --> 00:15:27,906
I'm not here to kill you.

206
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,080
I'm not moving.

207
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:31,967
Dech!

208
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:33,930
Dech!

209
00:15:41,423 --> 00:15:42,423
Kam!

210
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,120
Why are you doing this?!

211
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:47,200
It's the viscount's order.
I don't have a choice.

212
00:15:47,383 --> 00:15:48,983
Don't make this harder, Dech!

213
00:15:49,163 --> 00:15:50,796
I ran away this far.

214
00:15:50,997 --> 00:15:53,280
Why is he so vindictive toward me?!

215
00:15:53,657 --> 00:15:54,657
I'm sorry.

216
00:15:55,890 --> 00:15:57,017
I don't have a choice.

217
00:15:57,297 --> 00:15:58,640
He took Mai hostage.

218
00:15:58,890 --> 00:16:01,737
If I don't kiss Ms. Malai,
he will kill my son!

219
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:06,890
Dech.

220
00:16:07,317 --> 00:16:08,317
Dech!

221
00:16:17,523 --> 00:16:18,523
Dech!

222
00:16:23,897 --> 00:16:24,897
-Dech.
-Move!

223
00:16:28,543 --> 00:16:30,000
Don't be afraid, Ms. Malai.

224
00:16:31,077 --> 00:16:32,664
I won't let him kill you.

225
00:16:41,990 --> 00:16:44,043
I'm the only one
you're here to kill, right?

226
00:16:45,143 --> 00:16:46,143
Ms. Malai?

227
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,080
What are you doing?

228
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:53,237
If he's here just for me,

229
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:55,140
I'd rather let him kill me

230
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:57,360
and let you go.

231
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,680
So it's finally over, Dech.

232
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:03,917
We have nowhere else to run.

233
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:05,970
No, Ms. Malai.

234
00:17:06,470 --> 00:17:09,040
-I won't let you.
-But I don't want to run anymore.

235
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,640
I want this to end.

236
00:17:10,807 --> 00:17:14,240
Even if we keep running,
he will send someone to kill us.

237
00:17:14,453 --> 00:17:15,553
But I won't let you.

238
00:17:15,693 --> 00:17:18,040
If you die, I'll die with you.

239
00:17:20,187 --> 00:17:22,100
Dech! What are you doing?

240
00:17:22,353 --> 00:17:23,353
Dech.

241
00:17:23,817 --> 00:17:24,964
Move, I'm begging you.

242
00:17:25,165 --> 00:17:26,165
I'm not moving.

243
00:17:26,438 --> 00:17:29,496
If you're gonna shoot,
kill me along with Ms. Malai.

244
00:17:29,545 --> 00:17:30,545
I can't!

245
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:32,880
His Lordship wants you back!

246
00:17:34,313 --> 00:17:35,513
Or my son dies!

247
00:17:39,657 --> 00:17:40,657
Dech.

248
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:52,336
Ms. Malai,

249
00:17:53,696 --> 00:17:54,696
I'm sorry!

250
00:17:58,203 --> 00:17:59,203
Dech!

251
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:00,510
Dech!

252
00:18:10,730 --> 00:18:11,850
I said let go!

253
00:18:26,727 --> 00:18:28,180
Sounds like you're having fun.

254
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,800
Hello, Father.

255
00:18:34,987 --> 00:18:39,520
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

256
00:18:39,966 --> 00:18:44,513
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

257
00:18:50,897 --> 00:18:52,017
I said let go!

258
00:19:14,183 --> 00:19:15,183
Ms. Malai!

259
00:19:18,437 --> 00:19:20,440
After the sound of that gunshot,

260
00:19:20,597 --> 00:19:22,610
no one could predict

261
00:19:22,943 --> 00:19:24,280
if I lived or died.

262
00:19:25,883 --> 00:19:28,560
I will take you back
to your present

263
00:19:29,290 --> 00:19:30,790
so that you...

264
00:19:30,843 --> 00:19:33,159
get to see something...

265
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:34,560
unexpected.

266
00:19:52,510 --> 00:20:00,640
(1940)

267
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:05,603
Ms. Malai.

268
00:20:22,836 --> 00:20:23,836
Mai.

269
00:20:24,493 --> 00:20:25,493
-Mai.
-Rerai.

270
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,079
Mai! Mai!

271
00:20:28,453 --> 00:20:29,453
Mai!

272
00:20:29,813 --> 00:20:31,200
Mai? Mai?

